MAJOR AGREEMENTS
Reporton the interested-party
agreements entered into by Freight
One PJSC in 2020
According to the Federal Law on Joint-Stock Companies,
an interested-party agreement is one in which a member
of the Company’s Board of Directors, its single-person
executive body (the Chief Executive Officer), a member of
its collective executive body (the Management Board), or
a controlling entity of the Company, or an entity entitled
to issue the Company mandatory instructions, has an
interest.
An interested-party agreement does not require
mandatory approval in advance except where stipulated by
the Federal Law on Joint-Stock Companies.
Approval for an interested-party agreement may
be obtained in advance from the Company’s Board
of Directors or General Meeting of Shareholders, in
accordance with the Federal Law on Joint-Stock
Companies, at the request of the single-person executive
body, a member of the Company’s Management Board
or Board of Directors, or a shareholder (or shareholders)
holding at least 1 (one) percent of the Company’s voting
shares.

during the reporting period.
